HEADWORD: Doubly
<hw>Dou"bly</hw> <pr>(d⟦ucr⟧b"l⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>In twice the quantity; to twice the degree; <as>as, <ex>doubly</ex>
wise or good; to be <ex>doubly</ex> sensible of an
obligation.</as></def> <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Deceitfully.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A man that deals
